Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Brown sausage in a large skillet; drain and place sausage in a 9x13 inch baking dish. In a small bowl beat eggs; add flour, water and milk and beat all together. Let sit 5 minutes. Pour mixture over sausage and bake in preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until top is browned and crusty.